## A not-so-simple example {.smaller}

We can just as easily turn it into an animation, transitioning between dataset states!

::: columns
::: {.column width="50%"}


::: {.cell layout-align="center" output-location='column' hash='21-animation_cache/html/dino-5_4b852f3bcd8401bf64b77d0866c6d52a'}

```{.r .cell-code  code-line-numbers="6-13"}
datasaurus_dozen <- ggplot(
  datasaurus_dozen,
  aes(x, y, color = dataset)
) +
  geom_point(size = 2, show.legend = FALSE) +
  transition_states(
    dataset, 
    transition_length = 3, 
    state_length = 1
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "Dataset: {closest_state}"
  )
```
